704858f-a.title: Brooklyn: Henry Street - Huntington Street
704858f-a.text:
Henry Street, east side, north fromm Huntington Street. The
buildings are being torn down for the widening of Hamilton Avenue--
one block to the east --and its reconstructinn into a link in the
Belt Parkway system of roads.
October, 1940
P. L. Sperr

705057f-a.title: Brooklyn: Huntington Street - Henry Street
705057f-a.text:
75 Huntington Street, adjoining the N. W. corner of Henry Street,
showing a very old frame house, probably dating back to pre-Revolu-
tionary days.
October 23, 1940
P. L. Sserr
